## Class Hierarchy Summary

```
Object
  └── Staff (code, name)
        ├── Teacher  (subject, publication)
        ├── Officer  (grade)
        └── Typist   (speed)
              ├── RegularTypist (remuneration)
              └── CasualTypist  (dailyWages)

CallBase (callerName, callerNumber)
  ├── LocalCall  (durationMinutes, ratePerUnit)
  └── LongCall   (durationMinutes, callHour, originCode, destCode)
```

> **Key OOP Concepts Applied:**
> - ✅ **Encapsulation** — all instance variables `private`, accessed via getters/setters
> - ✅ **Inheritance** — `extends` used throughout hierarchy
> - ✅ **Polymorphism** — `@Override` on `displayInfo()`, Staff array demo
> - ✅ **Method Overloading** — three `abs()` methods in Program 1
> - ✅ **Constructors** — both default and parameterized in every class
> - ✅ **Input Validation** — negative checks on numeric fields
